tars stars above ~0.5 MSun appear to host\ndominantly axisymmetric fields with strong (kilo-Gauss) dipole components.\nBased on similarities between the magnetic properties of PMS stars and main\nsequence M-dwarfs with similar internal structures, we speculate that a\nbistable dynamo process operates for lower mass stars (<~0.5 MSun at an age of\na few Myr) and that they will be found to host a variety of magnetic field\ntopologies. If the magnetic topology trends across the HR diagram are confirmed\nthey may provide a new method of constraining PMS stellar evolution models.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 22 Jun 2012 19:53:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-05"}
